OL,3,CCould 'mental health ambulances' help
OL,4,Ckeep patients out of hospital?
OL,6,F"Sitting in front of them, having the
OL,7,Fright body language, active listening,
OL,8,Fhelps with de-escalation. So having
OL,9,Fthis environment is much better. And
OL,10,Fit means we don't need to keep one of
OL,11,Four huge trucks at scene, just to see
OL,12,Fthe patient."
OL,14,FAround 90% of patients are treated at
OL,15,Fscene in the new vehicles. After de-
OL,16,Fescalation, staff often refer patients
OL,17,Fto community-based services.
OL,19,FIn a standard ambulance without this
OL,20,Fspecialist support, only 40% of
OL,21,Fpatients are treated at scene.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
